    <div class="container">      
        <div class="content">
            <div class="summary-part">
                <h3>THE CHALLENGE</h3>
                <h4 class="program">I was tasked to analyze Lucie Glaister website and make suggestions on how to improve the overall usability as the client recognised there is a room for improvement. My main goal was to increase the engagement. It led me to redesigning the pages and extending the feature to allow users create profiles which are not functional on the current website and will be helpful for a client to obtain users emails and use the email to send a newsletter. I also focused on creating features when the user is able adding favorite products to the wishlist with a sharing option.</h4>
                <h3>METHOD</h3>
                <H4 style="font-weight: bold">Usability testing</H4>
                <h4>To test my assumptions of where the possible improvements lay, I focused on the following tasks: I conducted usability tests on 3 participants. They were 2 female and 1 male between the age 30 and 45 with a passion for high quality food.
                <h4>Purchase - Find the best food product with premium wine, chocolate and delicates. </h4>
                <h4>Subscribe to newsletter - People with passion for premium food, looking for not only handmade high quality food, but they also want to buy products which are made from seasonal food. </h4>
            </h4>
        </div>
    </div>

